      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented verification test suite and version-controlled release process consistent with MRL 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "The commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1) is accompanied by a published verification and validation manual, a regression test suite covering canonical flow benchmarks, and a formal software release process. Version control and change documentation are maintained by the software vendor. Achieved level 2 satisfies the required level for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through at least one canonical benchmark with known analytical or highly accurate reference solution.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was demonstrated using the lid-driven cavity benchmark at Re = 1000, comparing against the Ghia et al. reference solution. Velocity profiles along horizontal and vertical centerlines agreed to within 0.5% RMS. Taylor-Green vortex decay was also used to confirm temporal accuracy of the second-order implicit scheme. These results confirm correct numerical implementation at the level required for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Spatial discretization error must be quantified via a systematic mesh refinement study; GCI must be reported for the primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using mesh sizes of 2.1M, 5.8M, and 14.2M cells. Grid convergence index (GCI) for pressure rise at the 5 LPM / 3500 RPM operating point was 1.8%, well below the 5% threshold. The medium mesh (5.8M cells) was selected for production runs as it provides adequate accuracy with acceptable computational cost. Temporal convergence was confirmed by halving the time step and observing less than 0.3% change in cycle-averaged hemolysis index."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented with sufficient detail to allow assessment of representativeness relative to the COU.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark experimental dataset specifies fluid temperature (37°C), blood analog viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s), pump rotational speed (±10 RPM), and volumetric flow rate (±0.05 LPM) for each operating point. Test conditions are documented in the FDA Critical Path initiative report and are directly traceable to the COU operating envelope. Boundary conditions applied in the CFD model were matched to the documented experimental conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics must be reported for all primary quantities of interest; agreement must be within pre-specified acceptance thresholds.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison was performed for pressure rise (MAE 4.2%), velocity field (normalized RMS 6.8%), and relative hemolysis index (worst-case prediction 0.94 vs experimental 0.89 ± 0.06). All metrics satisfy pre-specified acceptance thresholds of 10% for pressure, 15% for velocity, and overlap with experimental uncertainty band for RH. Comparison methodology followed ASME V&V 20 procedures."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
