      "acceptanceCriteria": "The quantities of interest used in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical decision supported by the COU.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI, the relative hemolysis index RH, is the directly clinically relevant metric for the CPB device credibility assessment. Secondary QoIs (pressure rise, velocity field) support mechanistic understanding of hemolysis-generating flow features. All QoIs are defined in the COU and align with the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.0."
