    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors achieve their required levels for MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates that the CFD model predicts pressure rise, velocity fields, and relative hemolysis index within pre-specified acceptance thresholds across the full COU operating envelope. The worst-case hemolysis operating condition is correctly identified at 5.0 LPM / 3500 RPM with RH = 0.94, satisfying the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion with adequate margin. Six factors were not assessed per the MRL 2 assessment plan, consistent with the medium model influence and the availability of experimental testing to confirm results. The credibility assessment supports the regulatory decision that the CFD model provides adequate evidence for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
